URGENT SECURITY NOTICE

Dear Team Members,

Our security team has detected a sophisticated phishing campaign targeting our employees. Please read this carefully and take immediate action.

Threat Details:

Attack Type: Spear Phishing
Target: Company employees
Method: Fake IT support emails
Status: Active (detected 6 hours ago)
Affected: 12 employees clicked the link (accounts secured)

What the Phishing Email Looks Like:

Subject: "Urgent: Your Account Will Be Suspended"
From: "IT Support" <support@company-it.com> [FAKE]
Content: Claims your account will be suspended due to "suspicious activity"
Action: Asks you to click a link to "verify your identity"
Link: Leads to a fake login page that steals credentials

Red Flags to Watch For:
1. Urgent or threatening language
2. Sender email doesn't match company domain (@company.com)
3. Generic greetings ("Dear User" instead of your name)
4. Suspicious links (hover to see real URL)
5. Requests for passwords or sensitive information
6. Poor grammar or spelling errors

IMMEDIATE ACTIONS REQUIRED:

If You Clicked the Link:
1. Change your password IMMEDIATELY
2. Enable two-factor authentication (2FA)
3. Report to security@company.com
4. Check your account for unauthorized access
5. Monitor your email for suspicious activity

If You Received But Didn't Click:
1. Delete the email immediately
2. Report it to security@company.com
3. Do NOT forward it to colleagues
4. Mark as spam/phishing

Prevention Best Practices:

✓ Always verify sender email addresses
✓ Never click links in unexpected emails
✓ Use 2FA on all accounts
✓ Report suspicious emails immediately
✓ Attend mandatory security training (scheduled for Feb 5)
✓ Keep software and antivirus updated
✓ Use strong, unique passwords
✓ Be skeptical of urgent requests

Company Policy Reminder:
- IT will NEVER ask for your password via email
- We will NEVER threaten account suspension without prior notice
- All official communications come from @company.com domain
- When in doubt, call IT directly at ext. 2500

Security Measures Implemented:
- Enhanced email filtering
- Additional monitoring on all accounts
- Mandatory 2FA rollout (deadline: Jan 31)
- Security awareness training (Feb 5, mandatory)
- Incident response team on standby

Reporting:
If you receive ANY suspicious email:
1. Do NOT click any links
2. Forward to security@company.com
3. Delete the original email
4. Report via our Security Portal

Questions?
